x4freetext: The experiment was carried out using 11
MV tandem Pelletron accelerator at the University of
Notre Dame.
The gamma rays following the interaction in
the target were detected with a gamma-summing
detector SuN, developed at the National
Superconducting Cyclotron Laboratory, Michigan State
University. SuN is a NaI(Tl) cylinder, 16 in. in
diameter and 16 in. in length divided into eight
optically isolated segments. The volume of the
detector allows for total absorption of all the gamma
rays emitted during the reaction
Compiled by S.H.
